                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5045/385: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-09-24T15:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 24, 1926—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 24—10:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>429. My 419, September 20, 8 [<hi rend="italic">5</hi>] p.m. Following from
                    American consul general, Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“September 23, 4 p.m. Referring to my telegram of September 19, 4 p.m.
                            There were no pickets at Shameen gates today and indications are that
                            boycott as constituted during the last year is coming to end. It seems
                            certain however that British manufactured goods will still be under the
                            ban. Antiforeign feeling continues very widespread.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
